title: Strange
lyrics:
[Verse 1]
Strange, boy you're actin' shady
An unfamiliar taste on your lips lately
Tellin' me to calm down
Stop givin' me the runaround
Boy, you're so strange
Mmm, mmm, oh
[Chorus]
Boy, you're just a wannabe
Tryna be a comedy
But you're playin' with a tragedy
Boy, a big tragedy
[Post-Chorus]
Ooh, ooh, yeah
Ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh
Ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh, yeah, yeah, yeah
[Verse 2]
Strange way to start a conversation
Tellin' me you've changed
And now we're off to graduation
Tell me you know better
Got a jacket with a letter
But I'm not into high school things

[Chorus]
Boy, you're just a wannabe
Tryna be a comedy
But you're playin' with a tragedy
Boy, a big tragedy
[Post-Chorus]
Ooh, ooh, yeah
Ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh
Ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh, yeah, yeah, yeah
[Bridge]
You wanna be misunderstood
Got nothing underneath the hood
Drive Daddy's Bentley through the woods
A little bad could do you good
But you'll never make it out the woods
You don't want me like you wanna be
[Chorus]
Boy, you're just a wannabe
Tryna be a comedy
But you're playin' with a tragedy
Boy, a big tragedy
[Post-Chorus]
Ooh, ooh, yeah
Ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh
Ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh, yeah, yeah, yeah
